[{"id":"VR857472","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a vertically oriented mirror. A laser beam is directed towards the mirror from the top right at an angle of 30 degrees relative to the surface of the mirror. A dotted line extends horizontally from the mirror at the point where the laser beam reaches the mirror and the angle between the dotted line and the mirror is indicated as a right angle.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857472.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A laser beam is directed toward a vertical flat mirror at an angle of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"30 degrees\"><math alttext=\"30 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span> from the mirror’s surface, as shown in the figure. What is the angle of reflection as measured between the normal to the mirror's surface and the reflected beam?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857472_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"30 degrees\"><math alttext=\"30 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60 degrees\"><math alttext=\"60 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"120 degrees\"><math alttext=\"120 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>120</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"150 degrees\"><math alttext=\"150 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>150</mn><mo>°</mo></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]